text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. The film also stars Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, and Jude Law.

The film was announced at San Diego Comic-Con International 2016, with Brie Larson cast as Carol Danvers/Captain Marvel in July 2016. Filming began in January 2018, with a budget of around $152 million. The film was shot using Arri Alexa cameras, and was filmed on location in California, Louisiana, and Georgia.

Captain Marvel premiered in London on February 27, 2019, and was released in the United States on March 8, 2019. It received generally positive reviews from critics, who praised Larson's performance, the visual effects, and the action sequences. However, some critics felt that the story was formulaic and lacked depth. Despite this, the film was a commercial success, grossing over $1.1 billion worldwide, making it one of the highest-grossing films of 2019. A sequel, titled The Marvels, is currently in development, with Larson reprising her role.

## Plot

In 1989, Carol Danvers, a skilled Air Force pilot, crashes on Earth while testing an experimental aircraft. She is rescued by Nick Fury, a low-ranking S.H.I.E.L.D.
